# Windows Encoding

On Windows, never save repository text files as UTF-16 LE.

- Use Python `Path.write_text(content, encoding="utf-8")` for bulk or scripted writes.
- PowerShell: `Set-Content -Encoding utf8` or `[System.IO.File]::WriteAllText(path, content, New-Object System.Text.UTF8Encoding $false)`.
- After edits on Windows, run `python3 scripts/check-file-encoding.py` or `bash scripts/check-file-encoding.sh`.
- UTF-16 corruption breaks `.gitignore`, JSON, YAML, and `npm`/`json.load`.
